comments: Tatum (BOS) brings his arm down and makes contact to Burks' (PHI) arm/shoulder that affects his shot near the rim.
Theis (BOS) is already in Richardson's (PHI) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Theis (BOS) places his hand momentarily on Embiid's (PHI) side before immediately removing his hand.
Brown (BOS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Harris (PHI) in the post.
Theis (BOS) and Embiid (PHI) engage and separate under the rim during the rebound.
Embiid (PHI) dislodges Walker (BOS) from his rebounding position.
Theis (BOS) and Embiid (PHI) both move toward the same spot in the post as marginal contact occurs.
Smart (BOS) legally contests Richardson's (PHI) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Richardson (PHI) and Tatum (BOS) briefly engage and disengage off-ball.
Richardson (PHI) delivers contact with his lower body that affects Tatum's (BOS) driving shot attempt.
Embiid (PHI) and Smart (BOS) briefly engage and disengage as they position themselves for a potential rebound.
Harris (PHI) is already in Smart's (BOS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Brown (BOS) does not maintain legal guarding position and makes contact to Burks' (PHI) arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Theis (BOS) briefly grasps and releases Embiid's (PHI) arm during the rebound.
Tatum (BOS) and Embiid (PHI) make incidental contact with one another during rebounding.
Embiid (PHI) briefly gets tangled up with Tatum (BOS) in the backcourt and separates without affecting his FOM.
As Walker (BOS) is already falling down, marginal contact occurs from Embiid (PHI) that doesn't affect Walker's ability to complete the pass.
The Celtics legally advance the ball into the frontcourt within eight seconds.
Harris (PHI) attempts to commit a take foul on Walker (BOS), but contact is marginal.
Thybulle (PHI) moves laterally into Walker's (BOS) path and affects his SQBR.
Horford (PHI) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS).
